entry.def: You use not with verbs to form negative statements.

entry.def: You use not to form questions to which you expect the answer 'yes'.

example.ex: Why didn't you do it months ago?...

entry.def: You use not, usually in the form n't, in question tags after a positive statement.

example.ex: Not all the money, to put it mildly, has been used wisely...

example.ex: Not every applicant had a degree.
